<typeStatus id="E844881E6C0FE65C9177FEFAFCD85B2B" box="[806,861,351,372]" pageId="20" pageNumber="63">Type</typeStatus>
genus 
<taxonomicName id="F0FF4D3F6C0FE65C91E8FEFAFAAC5B2A" authority="Roder, 1892: 366" authorityName="Roder" authorityPageNumber="366" authorityYear="1892" box="[953,1321,351,373]" class="Insecta" family="Conopidae" genus="Brachyceraea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="058BEAAE6C0FE65C91E8FEFAFBD75B2B" box="[953,1106,351,372]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="63">Brachyceraea</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="536E4B4D6C0FE65C960FFEFAFAAC5B2A" author="Roder VV" box="[1118,1321,351,373]" pageId="20" pageNumber="63" pagination="366" refId="ref28786" refString="Roder VV. 1892. Brachyceraea nov. gen. novum genus Conopidarum (Diptera). Entomologische Nachrichten, Berlin 18: 366." type="journal article" year="1892">Röder, 1892: 366</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. Genera included: 
<taxonomicName id="F0FF4D3F6C0FE65C91F1FED8FBBC5BCD" authorityName="Roder" authorityYear="1892" box="[928,1081,381,402]" class="Insecta" family="Conopidae" genus="Brachyceraea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="058BEAAE6C0FE65C91F1FED8FBBC5BCD" box="[928,1081,381,402]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="63">Brachyceraea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="F0FF4D3F6C0FE65C9600FED8FC375BEE" authority="Krober, 1940 b: 217" authorityName="Krober" authorityPageNumber="217" authorityYear="1940" class="Insecta" family="Conopidae" genus="Microbrachyceraea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="058BEAAE6C0FE65C9600FED8FAAD5BCD" box="[1105,1320,381,402]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="63">Microbrachyceraea</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="536E4B4D6C0FE65C9768FED8FC375BEE" author="Krober O" pageId="20" pageNumber="63" pagination="203 - 245" refId="ref27228" refString="Krober O. 1940 b. Beitrage zur Kenntnis der Conopiden - VI. Annals and Magazine of Natural History Series 11, 5: 203 - 245." type="journal article" year="1940">Kröber, 1940b: 217</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="F0FF4D3F6C0FE65C919BFE39FA0C5BED" authority="Szilady, 1926: 587" authorityName="Szilady" authorityPageNumber="587" authorityYear="1926" box="[970,1417,412,434]" class="Insecta" family="Conopidae" genus="Neobrachyceraea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="058BEAAE6C0FE65C919BFE39FB0F5BEE" box="[970,1162,412,433]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="63">Neobrachyceraea</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="536E4B4D6C0FE65C96CEFE39FA0C5BED" author="Szilady Z" box="[1183,1417,412,434]" pageId="20" pageNumber="63" pagination="586 - 593" refId="ref30005" refString="Szilady Z. 1926. Dipterenstudien. Annales Musei Nationlis Hungarici 24: 586 - 593." type="journal article" year="1926">Szilady, 1926: 587</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. Uncontroverted morphological autapomorphy: scape quadrate (27). The single species of 
<taxonomicName id="F0FF4D3F6C0FE65C9684FE7CFCC85852" authorityName="Krober" authorityYear="1940" class="Insecta" family="Conopidae" genus="Microbrachyceraea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="058BEAAE6C0FE65C9684FE7CFCC85852" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="63">Microbrachyceraea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
possesses a quadrate scape and petiolate male abdomen, the two key characteristics of 
<taxonomicName id="F0FF4D3F6C0FE65C9743FDB3FCE45814" authorityName="ZIMINA" authorityYear="1960" class="Insecta" family="Conopidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Brachyceraeini">Brachyceraeini</taxonomicName>
, thereby warranting its inclusion.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="374036BC6C0FE65C916EFDF1FC2359A8" blockId="20.[806,1422,351,1107]" pageId="20" pageNumber="63">
The presently proposed membership of 
<taxonomicName id="F0FF4D3F6C0FE65C9740FDF1FCDA58D7" authorityName="ZIMINA" authorityYear="1960" class="Insecta" family="Conopidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Brachyceraeini">Brachyceraeini</taxonomicName>
matches the previously proposed definitions for the group. 
<bibRefCitation id="536E4B4D6C0FE65C91E4FD34FBEA58F8" author="Zimina LV" box="[949,1135,657,679]" pageId="20" pageNumber="63" pagination="723 - 733" refId="ref30406" refString="Zimina LV. 1960. New data on Conopidae system (Diptera) exemplified by the representatives of the USSR fauna. Zoologicheskii Zhurnal 39: 723 - 733." type="journal article" year="1960">Zimina’s (1960)</bibRefCitation>
original description of 
<taxonomicName id="F0FF4D3F6C0FE65C9177FD0AFC57589A" authorityName="ZIMINA" authorityYear="1960" box="[806,978,687,709]" class="Insecta" family="Conopidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Brachyceraeini">Brachyceraeini</taxonomicName>
includes the following diagnostic characters: antennae shortened; basisternum broad with very small posterolateral extensions; vein 
<collectionCode id="51EEAE796C0FE65C9732FD48FAF0595D" box="[1379,1397,749,770]" country="Chile" name="Departamento de Geologia, Universidad de Chile" pageId="20" pageNumber="63">R</collectionCode>
<subScript id="AB7B34F96C0FE65C9724FD52FA08595C" attach="left" box="[1397,1421,758,771]" fontSize="5" pageId="20" pageNumber="63">2+3</subScript>
parallel to 
<collectionCode id="51EEAE796C0FE65C91F5FCA9FC33597E" box="[932,950,780,801]" country="Chile" name="Departamento de Geologia, Universidad de Chile" pageId="20" pageNumber="63">R</collectionCode>
<subScript id="AB7B34F96C0FE65C91E7FCB0FC3B597E" attach="left" box="[950,958,789,801]" fontSize="5" pageId="20" pageNumber="63">1</subScript>
and meeting the costa midway between the end of 
<collectionCode id="51EEAE796C0FE65C91FAFC8FFC385960" box="[939,957,810,831]" country="Chile" name="Departamento de Geologia, Universidad de Chile" pageId="20" pageNumber="63">R</collectionCode>
<subScript id="AB7B34F96C0FE65C91EDFC91FC41591F" attach="left" box="[956,964,820,832]" fontSize="5" pageId="20" pageNumber="63">1</subScript>
and 
<collectionCode id="51EEAE796C0FE65C9657FC8FFB9D5960" box="[1030,1048,810,831]" country="Chile" name="Departamento de Geologia, Universidad de Chile" pageId="20" pageNumber="63">R</collectionCode>
<subScript id="AB7B34F96C0FE65C9646FC91FBB5591F" attach="left" box="[1047,1072,819,832]" fontSize="5" pageId="20" pageNumber="63">4+5</subScript>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="536E4B4D6C0FE65C9613FC8FFB6D591F" author="Hennig W" box="[1090,1256,810,832]" pageId="20" pageNumber="63" pagination="1 - 24" refId="ref26431" refString="Hennig W. 1966. Conopidae im Baltischen Bernstein (Diptera; Cyclorrhapha). Stuttgarter Beitrage zur Naturkunde 154: 1 - 24." type="journal article" year="1966">Hennig (1966)</bibRefCitation>
also suggests that the reduced antenna is probably a shared, derived apomorphy of the 
<taxonomicName id="F0FF4D3F6C0FE65C9608FCC2FB775923" authorityName="Roder" authorityYear="1892" box="[1113,1266,871,892]" class="Insecta" family="Conopidae" genus="Brachyceraea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="058BEAAE6C0FE65C9608FCC2FB775923" box="[1113,1266,871,892]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="63">Brachyceraea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The present analysis confirms that the characteristic antennal shape is due to a reduction in the scape. The other characters included by Zimina are plesiomorphic to 
<taxonomicName id="F0FF4D3F6C0FE65C9177FC44FC2759A8" authorityName="LATREILLE" authorityYear="1802" box="[806,930,993,1015]" class="Insecta" family="Conopidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Conopinae">Conopinae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="374036BC6C0FE65C916EFBA5FA805E0C" blockId="20.[806,1422,351,1107]" pageId="20" pageNumber="63">
Species examined – 
<taxonomicName id="F0FF4D3F6C0FE65C9609FBA5FA035E4A" authorityName="Loew" authorityYear="1847" box="[1112,1414,1024,1045]" class="Insecta" family="Conopidae" genus="Brachyceraea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevicornis">
<emphasis id="058BEAAE6C0FE65C9609FBA5FA035E4A" box="[1112,1414,1024,1045]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="63">Brachyceraea brevicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; 
<emphasis id="058BEAAE6C0FE65C9177FBBAFC025E0D" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="63">
<taxonomicName id="F0FF4D3F6C0FE65C9177FBBAFB2D5E6B" baseAuthorityName="Brunetti" baseAuthorityYear="1927" box="[806,1192,1055,1076]" class="Insecta" family="Conopidae" genus="Microbrachyceraea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pendleburyi">Microbrachyceraea pendleburyi</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName id="F0FF4D3F6C0FE65C969CFBBAFC025E0D" authorityName="Stuke &amp; Clements" authorityYear="2005" class="Insecta" family="Conopidae" genus="Neobrachyceraea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elongata">Neobrachyceraea elongata</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
; 
<taxonomicName id="F0FF4D3F6C0FE65C91C6FB98FB7B5E0D" baseAuthorityName="Krober" baseAuthorityYear="1913" box="[919,1278,1085,1106]" class="Insecta" family="Conopidae" genus="Neobrachyceraea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obscuripennis">
<emphasis id="058BEAAE6C0FE65C91C6FB98FB7B5E0D" box="[919,1278,1085,1106]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="63">Neobrachyceraea obscuripennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
